{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Bahrain National Stadium| <!--nickname = الوطني --> image = [[Image:Bahrain National Stadium.jpg|300px|center]]| fullname = Bahrain National Stadium | <!--fullname = Bahrain National Stadium |استاد البحرين الوطني--> location = [[Riffa]], [[Bahrain]] | built = 1981| opened = 1982| closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = |152 million dollars architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain National Football Team]], [[Riffa S.C.]] | seating_capacity = 30,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/bahrain/premier-league/20132014/regular-season/r22708/venues/?ICID=PL_3N_05|title=Venues - Premier League - Bahrain - Results, fixtures, tables and news - Soccerway|author=|date=|website=int.soccerway.com|accessdate=20 April 2018}}</ref>| dimensions = | }}
The '''Bahrain National Stadium''' ({{lang-ar|ستاد البحرين الوطني}}; [[Arabic transliteration|transliterated]]: Stād al-Bahrayn al-Watanī) is the [[national stadium]] of [[Bahrain]], located in East [[Riffa]]. It can accommodate 30,000 seats and is used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches.
It was built in 1982. The stadium was renovated in December 2012 for hosting the [[21st Arabian Gulf Cup]] tournament.
