{{Infobox football biography | name = Erene Bwakineti | image = | fullname = Erene Bwakineti | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1982|07|02}}<ref name="NFT" /> | birth_place = [[Kiribati]] | height = | position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]] | clubnumber = 13<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/Competitions/TeamList/tabid/1014/Competition/b4ecf3e8-9c15-42b7-847a-ee2a0e7a6296/language/en-US/Default.aspx |title=Kiribati Official Team List |work=oceaniafootball.com |publisher=Oceania Football Confederation |accessdate=25 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130210135456/http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/Competitions/TeamList/tabid/1014/Competition/b4ecf3e8-9c15-42b7-847a-ee2a0e7a6296/language/en-US/Default.aspx |archivedate=10 February 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | clubs1 = | caps1 = | goals1 = | pcupdate = 25 May 2013 | nationalyears1 = 2011&ndash; | nationalteam1 = [[Kiribati national football team|Kiribati]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | ntupdate = 25 May 2013 }}
'''Erene Bwakineti''' is an [[Gilbertese language|I-Kiribati]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]. He represents Kiribati at [[Kiribati national football team|international level]].<ref name="NFT">{{cite web | url = http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/44771/Erene_Bakineti.html| title = Erene Bakineti| work= national-football-teams.com |publisher=National Football Teams| accessdate = 25 May 2013}}</ref>
==International career== Bwakineti made three appearances at the [[Men's Football at the 2011 Pacific Games|2011 Pacific Games]] scoring one goal, in the 3-0 loss to [[Cook Islands national football team|Cook Islands]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/19a461c6-f66f-4e59-b45e-63a85c184b4f/language/en-US/Default.aspx |title=Cook Islands 3-0 Kiribati |author= |date=30 August 2011 |work=oceaniafootball.com |publisher=Oceania Football Confederation |accessdate=25 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130210163951/http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/19a461c6-f66f-4e59-b45e-63a85c184b4f/language/en-US/Default.aspx |archivedate=10 February 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> the 9-0 loss to [[Fiji national football team|Fiji]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/9da7e00d-a5b0-4990-9f93-462f2a9238c5/language/en-US/Default.aspx |title=Fiji 9 - 0 Kiribati |author= |date=30 August 2011 |work=oceaniafootball.com |publisher=Oceania Football Confederation |accessdate=25 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130210164136/http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/9da7e00d-a5b0-4990-9f93-462f2a9238c5/language/en-US/Default.aspx |archivedate=10 February 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> and in the 1-17 loss to [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]], where he scored in the 32nd minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/b89f0e50-3f24-474e-a008-ad1dfa24757f/language/en-US/Default.aspx |title=Kiribati 1 - 17 Tahiti |author= |date=4 September 2011 |work=oceaniafootball.com |publisher=Oceania Football Confederation |accessdate=25 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130210163625/http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/b89f0e50-3f24-474e-a008-ad1dfa24757f/language/en-US/Default.aspx |a