{{ infobox football league | name = Sub-County Leagues | image = | pixels = | country = {{flagicon|KEN}} [[Kenya]] | confed = [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] | founded = 10 July 2013<ref name="2014 system">{{cite web|title=New FKF soccer Structure to be implemented next year |url=http://www.michezoafrika.com/division-one/new-fkf-soccer-structure-to-be-implemented-next-year/13135 |date=10 July 2013 |author=Amos Abuga |publisher=MichezoAfrika.com |accessdate=11 July 2013}}</ref> | folded = | divisions = | teams = | feeds = | promotion = [[Kenyan County Champions League|County Champions League]] | relegation = | level = 6 | domest_cup = [[FKF President's Cup|President's Cup]] | confed_cup = | champions = | season = | most successful club = | tv = | website = | current = }}
The '''Kenyan Sub-County Leagues''' are the sixth and lowest tier of the [[Kenyan football league system]]. They have a promotion and relegation system with the [[Kenyan County Champions League]]. Member clubs are [[Amateur sports|amateur]].
The leagues were formed on 10 July 2013 in line with the introduction of a new six-tier system by the [[Football Kenya Federation]] to take effect from the beginning of the [[2014 in Kenyan football|2014 season]].<ref name="2014 system" />
==See also== * [[Kenyan football league system]]
