{{use dmy dates|date=July 2014}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = MLT | NOCname = [[Malta Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1960 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.nocmalta.org }} | location = [[Rome]] | competitors = 10 | sports = 4 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Malta]]''' competed at the '''[[1960 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Rome]], [[Italy]]. Ten competitors, all men, took part in six events in four sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/MLT/summer/1960/ |title=Malta at the 1960 Rome Summer Games |accessdate=29 July 2014 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref> The nation returned to the Olympic Games after a 12-year absence, since [[1948 Summer Olympics|1948]].
==Cycling== {{main article|Cycling at the 1960 Summer Olympics}} Three cyclists represented Malta in 1960.
;[[Cycling at the 1960 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|Individual road race]] * [[Paul Camilleri]] * [[John Bugeja]] * [[Joseph Polidano]]
;[[Cycling at the 1960 Summer Olympics – Men's team time trial|Team time trial]] * [[John Bugeja]] * [[Paul Camilleri]] * [[Joseph Polidano]]
==Sailing== {{main article|Sailing at the 1960 Summer Olympics}}
==Shooting== {{main article|Shooting at the 1960 Summer Olympics}} Two shooters represented Malta in 1960.
;[[Shooting at the 1960 Summer Olympics – Men's trap|Trap]] * [[Wenzu Vella]] * [[Joseph Grech (sport shooter)|Joseph Grech]]
==Swimming== {{main article|Swimming at the 1960 Summer Olympics}}
