{{Infobox football club | nickname = | ground = | capacity = | season = [[2017–18 Lebanese Premier League|2017-18]] | clubname = Salam Sour | image = [[File:Salam_Sour_(logo).png|logo]] | fullname = Salam Sour Sports Club | founded = 1961 | chairman = | manager = | league = [[Lebanese Third Division]] | position = 7th | website = }}
'''Salam Sour Sports Club''' (in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] '''نادي السلام الرياضي صور''') is a Lebanese [[association football|football]] club headquartered in [[Tyre, Lebanon|Tyre]] in South Lebanon.
The club's ascent to the [[Lebanese Premier League]] was very quick as the it became champions of [[Lebanese Third Division]] in the 2008-2009 season, and promoted to the [[Lebanese Second Division]]. The following [[2009–10 Lebanese Second Division|season]] Salam Sour became the champion of the division and was promoted to the Premier League. Today, the club competes in the Lebanese Third Division.
[[Category:Football clubs in Lebanon]] {{Lebanon-footyclub-stub}}

